reviewText:
Less than 1 hour into game and I had enough.
All the bugs that put me off outright:
*gimmicky movement - during second pre-quest sliding didn't work properly (character was periodically descending);
*audio desync - frequent massive audio delay after firing rifle, at times also no sound from enemy weapons, just bullets hitting target impact sound;
*impossible to close menu with cursor at times - it says to close it with esc - it fails to mention you are forced to look at all leveling up perks (blue symbol at left corner). Figuring that and running to second quest cursor menu again popped up and I had to franticly smash esc and n to close it. After 30 seconds of smashing it closed. During second quest before upcoming mob wave I opened inventory, closed it but cursor menu again didn't close, this time with no luck to close it.
That's the first game behaving like that, all the other games work fine on my PC.

CONS::

- P2W;
- Cubehead developers who don't listen to feedback or bug reports and release content anyway;
- Crate system à la Team Fortress 2/CS:GO, but with non-cosmetic items which you can't find otherwise; opening a crate for free requires months of grind;
- Dead/dying/nonexistent community, most of the time it feels like you're playing a really bland and buggie singleplayer game with a constant feeling that you're just beating a dead horse;
- BUGS! FIND'EM, LOVE'EM, GET USED TO'EM! The main reason why you will quit this game;
- The game mounts are only rentable, without any option to buy them;
- Slow, boring, snail-paced game; if you're expecting a fast-paced FPS game, like Quake, move on;
- PVP is dead, takes 4 eons to find a match, and if you do, someone will crash or disconnect anyway;
- Half of the original content got shelved, because reasons;
- Etc.

PROS::

- It had potential in beta;

CONCLUSION::

- RIP
